Overview

The Peugeot 208 is sold here in four variants and two different bodystyles - 3-door and 5-door hatchback. Prices for this French hatchback range from RM83,432 to RM136,082.Competition for this model comes in the form of the Mazda 2 Hatchback, Suzuki Swift, Proton Iriz, Ford Fiesta Hatchback, Kia Rio, Honda Jazz and Chevrolet Sonic Hatchback. The range topping 208 GTi on the other hand takes on hot hatches like the Ford Fiesta ST and Renault Clio RS200 EDC. 

Under the hood of all the 208 variants except the GTi is a naturally aspirated 1.6-litre four-cylinder petrol engine that kicks out a respectable 122hp at 6,000rpm and 160Nm of torque at 4,250rpm. Drive is sent to the wheels via a four-speed Tiptronic transmission. Peugeot claims the car can return a fuel economy figure of 6.7-litres per 100km. 

The hot GTi variant on the other hand features a turbocharged 1.6-litre petrol four-pot that sends 200hp and 275Nm of twist to the front wheels through a six-speed manual tranny. It is capable of doing the century sprint in just under seven seconds, while top speed is rated at 230km/h. This models als comes with some performance enhancing goodies such a sports exhaust, a bodykit, a performance oriented suspension tuning as well as larger brakes and wheels. 
